04/01/2009
BUCHAREST, Romania/ATHENS, Greece/ANKARA, Turkey/TIRANA, Albania/SKOPJE. Macedonia -- Temperatures as low as -20 degrees Celsius hit Romania on Saturday (January 3rd). Eastern Turkey and northern Greece also suffered a cold snap. Meanwhile, motorists in northern Albania and throughout Macedonia struggled with blizzard-caused road closures and traffic delays. (Agerpres, ANA-MPA, Anadolu news agency, MINA, Makfax, MIA - 03/01/09)
